## In Go it's a lot more work

<br>

```
t=$(tempfile -s .go)
```
<br>

**Write your program into the temporary file**

<br>

```
echo 'package main
import "fmt"
func main(){fmt.Println(6*7)}' > $t
```

: You need at least
: - a package statement,
: - an import statement
: - and a main function

